                  <decoDesc>
                     <decoNote resp="#DL #PA">Important miniatures, historiated and other borders, initials. Illumination, unfinished, by at least three French hands, of whom Pächt and Alexander identified one from the
                        <persName role="art" key="person_4811651">Jacquemart d'Hesdin</persName> atelier, fols. 51v and 63, and the <persName role="art" key="person_316450919"><!-- as Maitre de Lucon -->Master of Étienne
                           Loypeau</persName>, fol. 171v (P&amp;A i.
            637, pl. XLIX).</decoNote>
                     <decoNote resp="#DL">Most of the miniatures and their outer borders were added by the <persName role="art" key="person_95739617">Master of the Brussels Initials</persName> (formerly known as Zenobi da Firenze)</decoNote>
                  </decoDesc>
                  <bindingDesc>
                     <binding resp="#DL"  notAfter="1834" notBefore="1750">
                        <p>Red velvet, rebacked with red 'plush', probably for Douce.</p>
                     </binding>
                  </bindingDesc>
